This standing eagle hip opener, at times seems to be a really hard !! Esply when the hips are not warmed up enough!! 
Yogidandasana itself is quite a hip opener!! I surely find it much easier to first sit , get the feet on the right spot under the arm and then try and open up!! 

Yeah it’s not pretty or perfect or fancy looking when taken support!! But trust me when I say all the fancy beautiful yoga postures that we see on Social media once started taking support , proper dedication and most importantly years of practice ❤️❤️!! 

My humble request to all the fresh buds on Instagram!! Please try the journey first else the injuries can be dangerous!! 🙏🏻🙏🏻

Good morning 🌞 one little yoga flow that I make it a must to include in my everyday pregnancy is this!! 

Reclined hero to shoulderstand to plough pose to bridge to wheel and back to hero’s !! When your shoulders, neck and spine are healthy you are healthy too!!

Hello there 🙏🏻 Are you in your third term and still going to work physically 😊!! WELL ITS NOT A BAD THING but you have to keep few things in mind, to make this experience towards your benifits‼️

Third term Office care:👇🏻

✅ Always support your lower belly when you walk!! Either wear a pregnancy support belt or just use your hands. Your lower belly gets even more heavier, thanks to gravity, and that could really hurt your back and hips. 

✅Surely make sure to get up frequently and stretch your back. Find a wall and support your spine on it. Gently take your hands up all the wall and stretch your whole body. This will lengthen your spine and allow some space for your organs and lungs to breathe as of to sitting constantly. 

✅Find a couch or a comfortable chair with cushion on which you can keep your tail bone straight but stretch your upper back, dropping your hands and chest on either sides, opening up your rib cages. This will relax your upper belly and chest muscles really well. 

✅Do not forgot to elevate your feet and rotate your ankle whenever you can while sitting at work to avoid numbness and increase blood flow. Swelling of feet and ankle pain is very common and this simple movement can surely help prevent it. 

Happy working ❤️🙏🏻

Every pregnant body is different and with different strength!! So take it easy without comparing and do what is best for you.!! 

Two lovely labour prep, prenatal practice one can include: 
1. Frog Pose / Mandukasana 🙏🏻
2. Puppy Pose / Uttana Shishosana 🙏🏻

Both of these does a great job in strengthening the hip muscles running down the legs and opening up the pelvic floor!! In addition it can also expand the chest and ease out lower back strain🙏🏻

One thing to keep in mind, when practicing these , be very sure not to PRESS or TOUCH the belly on the floor‼️

Breathe gently and enjoy the stretch!! 
Have a lovely day ❤️

It is important to keep flowing your energy no matter how difficult it gets ‼️
Recently I learnt trying to let the energy flow all along from head to toe in your last couple of weeks of pregnancy, can surely make the mother feel more relaxed and destressed even with all the crazy pains and anxieties within‼️
.
.
Uttanasana, one of the crucial yoga posture in prenatal practice can be a great resource to open up and practice safely at this time. 
👉🏻 Take the circles as slow as you need to 
👉🏻 opening up the chest as much as you can
👉🏻 pushing your hips lower and backward when in a chair
👉🏻 Only if you can , go all the way to purna skandasana for more hip opening and groin pains. 

Repeat till you feel good and listen to your body‼️ Take all the surrounding supports needed and keep breathing🙏🏻❤️
.
.
.

Three easy standing movements that you can try safely in your 38th 39th week🙏🏻

1. Put your hands in front of you and deeply breathe opening up your lungs completely, pushing your arms back with slight backbend ‼️

2. Standing hip distance apart, gently rotating your head in full or half circles, trying to release all the neck and shoulder tension‼️

3. With feet apart trying to squat in a goddess position as much as your body allows you too. Keeping your hips open and supporting your legs‼️

Practice slowly and safely 🙏🏻🙏🏻

Most of us have this notion , with C section it’s very difficult to loose weight or go back to our pre pregnancy body. 

Well honestly I do not know how true is this since I haven’t started my weight loss journey yet. 
Recovering from C section can take months, but what we all new momies can start right away are these three things which surely helps a lot , kickstarting our transformation without have to do any exercise or strict diet initially :

1. Breastfeeding or breast pumping can loose upto 500 calories each day, depending on how much you are able to do, also contracting your uterus to get back to its normal size, hence flattening the lower belly 😃

2. Keeping yourself hydrated almost thrice the amount one will usually consume. This not only takes care of lactation, painful contractions but also helps with metabolism. 

3. Lastly, start wearing the postpartum belt for supporting your core and abdominal muscles as long as you every day for atleast 12 weeks. 

Three non workout tips which can help make you feel better 😍 again every body is different so give it time 🙏🏻

#postpatrum #postpartumfitness #yoga #yogapractice #corestrengthening #pelvisstability #postdelivery #legstrength #buildbackbetter #reels #reelsinstagram #reelsvideo #yogagram #squat #🙏🏻

Here👇🏻

🫶🏻 C section Moms will have a very difficult time bending side ways!! So wait for the complete healing ❤️‍🩹 

🫶🏻Once you can, grab whatever support you can find around you for leg extensions!! That will instantly initiate your hamstring muscle strength. 

🫶🏻 once comfortable, try and grab your feet slowly bending side ( since that is way easier than bending front) , and you can start feeling your hamstring pains. 

🫶🏻Once comfortable holding your big toe, now slowly try and rotate your chest upwards with a gentle twist as it increases blood flow in your leg muscles. 

🫶🏻Stay as long as you can with deep breathing in this Parivratta Uttanasana or revolved side bend fold. Start with standing first, that is easier on hamstring!! When really comfortable, go for the actual sitting ones. 

👉🏻PS: Hamstrings looses their flexibility way faster than other body parts, for me, I have not practiced any hamstring workouts during my prenatal so clearly they are dead. 🙈!! 

Take it slow !! AVOID INJURIES !! Listen to your post delivery body, trust me it’s no way near the same 😬!!

Happy healing ❤️‍🩹 
.
.

Postpartum fitness👇🏻

We need to remember every body type is different and work’s differently. 
For me, I have slowly started including dolphin or ardhapinchamayurasana to increase or retain back my arms shoulders and wrist strength. 
The core tor sure is taking a lot more time but these three dolphin workouts can work wonders over the time. 

1. Dolphin chin press.  Most likely 10 of 2 sets. Here is where the fire really gets activated and your shoulders and forearms builds back

2. Dolphin leg press. You can do as many as you want. This is quite excellent for the pelvic floor , tonning back the lower body and getting your hip joints to shrink back. 

3. Dolphin leg splits. This is one of my favorite dolphin stretch. This targets your entire body at one go. Hold as long as you can and enjoy the benifits. 

If yours is a C section like me, then for sure wait atleast 12 weeks to start these and take lots of precautions around the lower belly. Any stress pull etc , release right away and rest. 

Happy healing 💗

Everyone is different so the time each one of us take will VARRY for sure!! But honestly women standing up on their feet in no time after C section only inspires me to get moving but at the same time listening to my body and working out accordingly is also important.

I often get texts on do s and don’ts post C section, and to all the beautiful new mommies, I can only tell you from what I experienced👇🏻
I CAN NOT HOLD BACKBENDS AND PLANKS FOR LONGER TIME

I started practicing headstands after 20 weeks post C section with wall support and now after 24 weeks I can hold it for 45 secs with variations. Yes I am trembling and need wall behind me for mental support but with each day it just gets better . 

Often women gets depressed thinking of their pre pregnancy self and lacks confidence with their social presence. Let’s accept everyone is different but accepting your post pregnancy self with confidence is what we should all aim for.
